text: Orbital's Antares rocket exploded just after launch last night. (unmanned, no deaths on site). It was supposed to resupply the ISS. spectator video: <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3jCystkiIBs> more story: <http://www.theregister.co.uk/2014/10/29/whoops_orbital_sciences_antares_iss_resupply_mission_blows_up_just_after_launch/>

Elon's quote from 2 years ago: "One of our competitors, Orbital Sciences, has a contract to resupply the International Space Station, and their rocket honestly sounds like the punch line to a joke. It uses Russian rocket engines that were made in the ’60s. I don’t mean their design is from the ’60s—I mean they start with engines that were literally made in the ’60s and, like, packed away in Siberia somewhere."
Ironically, the practice of Project Management as we know it (standards, processes, etc) got its starts in the 50s with the space program.
